n with homosexuality, and shows how these proposed solutions are either inadequate or positively dangerous. According to the author, the time has come for "gaytheism": leaving religion behind in order to preserve queer dignity, rights, and lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHomosexualityxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aHomosexualityzUnited States. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845113840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438451138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438451138/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles